      "writtenOn": "2017-10-30T20:23:58Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "nit: This might not work well if there are multiple failures. sk.errorMessage will only show the last error. Suggestions:\nA. Don\u0027t worry about it.\nB. Collect the Promises from _cancel, then do something like:\nPromise.all(...).catch(function () {\n  sk.errorMessage(\"Failed to cancel one or more jobs.\");\n});\nC. Collect the successes and failures, then display a popup indicating which were canceled and which were not.",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 250,
        "startChar": 10,
        "endLine": 250,
        "endChar": 38
      },
      "revId": "b1b3f76522ed9545c9e154efe3765149f19216dd",
